        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:3:91:2",
        "text": [
          " لَا يَرْتَمِسُ الْمُحْرِمُ فِي الْمَاءِ وَ لَا الصَّائِمُ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Al Husayn, from Safwan, from Yaqoub Bin Shuayb, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Neither the one in <span class=\"iTxt\">Ihraam</span> nor the Fasting one can immerse himself into the water’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Muhammad ibn al-Husayn from Safwan from Ya’qub ibn Shu’ayb who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘One in the state of Ihram must not submerge his head in the water, as well as one fasting.’” "
          ]
        }
